DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("LimitedNumeric");

$b=random(2,9,1);
$a=random(2,9,1);
$c=random(2,9,1);

$ans=Compute($a*($b)+$c);


##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Evaluate the expression:

    [`` [$c]+[$a]([$b])=  ``]  [________]{$ans} 

END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

Since there is no operation symbol between [`[$a]`] and [`([$b])`], it implies multiplication.

We perform multiplication first, as multiplication has a higher priority than addition.

      [``
        \begin{aligned}[t]
           [$c]+[$a]([$b]) & = [$c]+[$a*$b] \\
                                 & =  [$ans] 
          \end{aligned}
      ``]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();


